content.text:
Mr. TOOMEY. Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the Senate 
proceed to legislative session and be in a period of morning business, 
with Senators permitted to speak therein for up to 10 minutes each, 
after which the Senate stand adjourned under the previous order.
content.speaker: Mr. TOOMEY

content.text: The PRESIDING OFFICER. Without objection, it is so ordered.
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER
